BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:0cc4c9fb-5ce6-5d29-9494-a9d219ea8bc4
SUMMARY:Beyond the Net Grant Program
DESCRIPTION:The Internet Society Foundation’s Beyond the Net Grant Program offers fu
 nding to support Internet Society Chapters to implement innovative proje
 cts that make a local impact by providing meaningful access to an open\,
  trusted\, and globally-connected Internet\, as well as strengthening th
 e Chapters’ presence in the surrounding community.
URL:https://www.isocfoundation.org/grant-programme/beyond-the-net-grant-program/
DTSTAMP:20240101T000000Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20261015
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20261015
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:7fa2ffd5-293d-5bf6-899e-8afc110ea08a
SUMMARY:Internet Governance Forum Events Funding
DESCRIPTION:The Internet Society Foundation’s Internet Governance Forum (IGF) fundin
 g program supports the organization of United Nations (UN) IGF Secretari
 at-recognized National and Regional Initiatives (NRIs) and National and 
 Regional Schools on Internet Governance. The purpose of the IGF is to en
 courage open\, non-commercial\, and inclusive multi-stakeholder dialogue
  on issues related to Internet governance. The goal of Schools on Intern
 et Governance is to ensure that diverse actors have the skills to partic
 ipate in Internet governance structures and shape the future of the Inte
 rnet.
URL:https://www.isocfoundation.org/grant-programme/internet-governance-forum-events/
DTSTAMP:20240101T000000Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20261015
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20261015
END:VEVENT
