BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:f820c1cb-3c90-52e3-8e30-18f0edf9e630
SUMMARY:Learning@ Internet Society
DESCRIPTION:Our courses provide you with practical technical skills designed and del
 ivered by Internet experts. You will gain knowledge and skills on how th
 e Internet works\, how it is governed\, and how to keep the Internet and
  its users safe and secure.
URL:https://www.internetsociety.org/learning/
DTSTAMP:20240101T000000Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20261231
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20261231
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:ec39ebb2-5714-5559-9884-b31d90831ab8
SUMMARY:Regional Working Groups
DESCRIPTION:Our Regional Working Groups are community‑led spaces\, facilitated by a 
 community expert. Internet Society members and staff discuss and collabo
 rate on Internet policy and advocacy connected to four key themes: Safer
  Internet\, Connectivity\, Open Internet\, Internet Governance. These gr
 oups enable you to get directly involved with the issues that matter mos
 t to you. You can also connect with peers across your region\, exchange 
 knowledge\, and contribute to practical outputs such as policy briefs\, 
 consultations\, research\, and community events.
URL:https://www.internetsociety.org/community/news/join-a-regional-working-group/
DTSTAMP:20240101T000000Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20261231
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20261231
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:a14cbb63-0929-5f41-b964-2c9b6bc5c1ca
SUMMARY:Moderated Courses- Learning @Internet Society
DESCRIPTION:Moderated courses are offered through the Learning @ Internet Society on
 line platform\,\nsupported by a moderator and a tutor. The moderator ens
 ures all administrative issues are\naddressed\, and the tutor provides t
 he technical expertise and answers all questions related\nto the subject
  matter.
URL:https://www.internetsociety.org/learning/
DTSTAMP:20240101T000000Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260719
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260719
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:d72143c7-ff87-50e2-bf1a-e11a8c7bb2a7
SUMMARY:Chapters Capacity Building Program 2026
DESCRIPTION:The Chapters Capacity Building Program 2026 is a training series for Int
 ernet Society chapter leaders\, delivered by Nonprofit Builder\, offered
  at no cost for Internet Society chapters\, online across four tracks — 
 Impact Measurement\, Conflict Resolution\, Leadership & Governance\, and
  Financial Management — as weekly 2-hour workshops from June to October 
 2026\, in English\, French\, and Spanish.
URL:https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSedxE-AHa8mjh-2ggVzzztxr-buE1caKgH05dQvO9POY4xM4w/viewform
DTSTAMP:20240101T000000Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260716
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260716
END:VEVENT
